From 6b7ac7cf29e25966a399fd072406f7b305b79901 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Apr 2026 05:10:35 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add XSD datatype propagation for typed literals

- SQLValue: add virtual datatypeIRI() returning the XSD type URI for
  the value, or empty string for plain string literals (default).
- TermMap: add virtual computeDatatypeIRI(row) that returns the static
  rr:datatype from the mapping if present, falling back to empty string.
- ColumnTermMap: override computeDatatypeIRI to delegate to the column
  value's datatypeIRI() when no static rr:datatype is set in the mapping.
- PredicateObjectMap::processRow: call computeDatatypeIRI for literal
  object maps (no language tag) and pass the resulting datatype SerdNode
  to serd_writer_write_statement.  The dtIRI std::string is declared in
  the enclosing scope so its buf pointer remains valid across the write.

https://claude.ai/code/session_01ST2afWuuG4YrfZ6rs9EsEE
